<font color="#FF0000">RAP WITH GARY</font><br>
<tt>Wed Dec 10 11:17:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Gary,<br><br>
I'm not sure what numbers you are talking about on my steel pot.  I was a Wolfhound (Alpha and Delpha companies of the 27th Infantry).  You hit a lot of buttons about fear and rage being sharp edges of the same knife.<br><br>
We rarely saw who was shooting at us.  Lots and lots of booby traps.  I remember being pulled out of places because they were so &quot;thick.&quot;<br><br>
I believe that combat time in war can only be understood by personal experience.  Fear, desperation, anger, exhaustion, depression and bravado are only a few of the attitudes and feelings that one has to deal with when living on the edge.<br><br>
Good to talk to you.  You have a lot to add to this site.<br><br>
Paul
